'''布里爾'''（bril）是一個[[心理物理学|心理物理学]]上的[[明度|明度]]單位。

布里爾定義為在[[亮度|亮度]]一微[[朗伯_(單位)|朗伯]]的區域，適應黑暗的眼睛可以接受到的明度<ref name="StevensMarks">J.C. Stevens, L.E. Marks: ''Stevens’s Power Law in Vision: Exponents, Intercepts, and Thresholds.'' In: ''Fechner Day 99: Proceedings of the Fifteenth Annual Meeting of the International Society for Psychophysics''. 1999, S. 82–87 ([http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Lawrence_Marks2/publication/266870805_STEVENS%27S_POWER_LAW_IN_VISION_EXPONENTS_INTERCEPTS_AND_THRESHOLDS/links/546dd8330cf26e95bc3d02c9.pdf online] {{Wayback|url=http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Lawrence_Marks2/publication/266870805_STEVENS%27S_POWER_LAW_IN_VISION_EXPONENTS_INTERCEPTS_AND_THRESHOLDS/links/546dd8330cf26e95bc3d02c9.pdf |date=20151120073029 }}): „One bril is the brightness produced by 40 dB re 10<sup>-10</sup> lambert [0.003 cd/m<sup>2</sup>] in a dark-adapted eye.“ (d. h. die 1 Bril verursachende Leuchtdichte liegt um einen Faktor 10000 (40 [[dB|dB]]) über der Referenzleuchtdichte 10<sup>−10</sup> Lambert)</ref><ref name="vandenBrink">
G. van den Brink: ''Subjective Brightness during Dark-Adaptation.'' In: ''Vision Research.'' 2, Nr. 12, 1962, S. 495–502, [[doi:10.1016/0042-6989(62)90051-2|doi:10.1016/0042-6989(62)90051-2]]: „A bril is defined as the brightness seen by a dark-adapted observer when he views a luminance of 40 decibels (dB).“</ref><ref group="註" name="Mikrolambert" />。

人感受到的明度和物體表面的亮度不是成正比，像[[古斯塔夫·费希纳|古斯塔夫·费希纳]]提出的[[韋伯-費希納定理|韋伯-費希納定理]]及{{le|斯坦利·史密斯·史蒂文斯|Stanley Smith Stevens}}提出的{{le|斯蒂文斯冪律|Stevens' power law}}一様。

因為眼睛在不同的亮度會調整其對光的靈敏度，因此感受到的明度會和{{le|眼睛光适应|Adaptation (eye)}}有關。

